Blaine.Blaine High School (Minnesota):
Blaine High School is a public high school in Blaine, Minnesota as part of the Anoka-Hennepin School District 11. The school was opened in 1972, as part of the Blaine Project.
As of the 2014-15 school year, the school had an enrollment of 2,865 students and 122.4 classroom teachers (on an FTE basis), for a student–teacher ratio of 23.4:1.
